{"word":"ἄνηθον","slug":"ἄνηθον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄνηθον</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> unknown.\n<p/><i>anise, dill</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; ionic <el>ἄννησον</el> or <el>ἄνησον</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; aeolic <el>ἄννητον</el>, or <el>ἄνητον</el>, <b><a href='S:Sappho Lyrica'>Sapph.</a></b>.<p/>"}]}